<DocsPageTitle Path="Extensions/Maps">
    Blazorise Maps component
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Display interactive maps with tile layers, markers, and geographic shapes.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    The Maps extension follows the same abstraction principles as the rest of Blazorise: applications work with Blazorise components and models instead of being coupled directly to a JavaScript map library.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Leaflet is currently used as the first map provider. The public API is intentionally provider-neutral so additional providers can be supported over time without changing the component model used by applications.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    To use the <Code>Map</Code> component, install the <Code>Blazorise.Maps</Code> package first.
</DocsPageParagraph>

